# UI style boundaries: Chakra v3 / Ark UI vs Tailwind v4

This template is the reference starter for HandCash apps. The UI stack is
layered, and each layer has one job. Forks that follow these rules avoid the
preflight, sizing, contrast, label, and dismissal regressions that prompted
the boundary in the first place. Follow them when authoring or editing
anything in `components/ui/*` or any styled component.

## Layer responsibilities

| Layer | Owner | Job |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Behavior + a11y + state machines | Ark UI (via Chakra v3) | Open/close, focus trap, keyboard nav, ARIA, controlled state |
| Tokens (colors, radii, fonts, shadows) | CSS variables in `app/globals.css` | One source of truth, read by Tailwind, Chakra system, and raw CSS |
| Visual styling | Tailwind v4 utility classes via `className` | Backgrounds, borders, spacing, typography, layout |
| Compatibility shape | `components/ui/*` wrappers | Translate Ark/Chakra into a shadcn/Radix-shaped API for consumers |

## Hard rules

1. **Chakra preflight stays off.** `lib/chakra/system.ts` sets `preflight: false`.
   Tailwind v4 owns the base reset; do not let Chakra inject a second one.
2. **No Chakra style props.** Inside `components/ui/*`, never use Chakra style
   props (`bg`, `color`, `p`, `mt`, `borderColor`, `_hover`, etc.) on Chakra
   components — every visual choice goes on `className` as a Tailwind utility.
3. **No hardcoded hex / rgb.** Read from CSS variables: `bg-primary`,
   `text-foreground`, `border-border`. New tokens go in `app/globals.css`
   first, get a Tailwind alias under `@theme inline`, then get a Chakra
   `semanticTokens` entry in `lib/chakra/system.ts` if Chakra internals need it.
4. **Keep `data-slot`.** Every wrapper component sets `data-slot="..."` so
   product code can target it with Tailwind selectors and the previous
   shadcn-shaped CSS keeps working.
5. **Conditional-render dismissal.** Dialog, DropdownMenu, and Popover
   wrappers pass `open` / `onOpenChange` straight through to Chakra. The
   `*Content` components read `useDialogContext()` / `useMenuContext()` /
   `usePopoverContext()` and `return null` when `open` is false — this
   bypasses Chakra's presence machinery so React unmounts immediately and
   we never get stuck dialogs, menus, or popovers. Inside menu items,
   queue `menu.setOpen(false)` in a `queueMicrotask` after the consumer's
   `onClick` as a belt-and-suspenders backstop for React 19 batching.
   Consumers pass `open` / `onOpenChange` straight through and trust the
   wrapper; do not reinvent internal mirrors.
6. **No Chakra recipes for our visual styling.** If a recipe insists on a
   shape that fights Tailwind (e.g. Avatar's enforced size), drop down to
   `@ark-ui/react/<part>` directly inside the wrapper.
7. **Forward `className` last.** Always merge with `cn()` and place the
   consumer's `className` at the end so it can override wrapper defaults.
8. **Tark UI pattern for primitives Chakra v3 doesn't ship.** When Chakra
   v3 doesn't expose a usable primitive (currently: Tour, Tags Input, Steps,
   Editable, Number Input with stepper, Color Picker, Signature Pad,
   Tree View), copy raw `@ark-ui/react/<part>` components styled with
   Tailwind utilities into `components/ui/*` following the Tark UI reference
   (<https://tarkui.com>, anubra266/tarkui — Ark UI + Tailwind copy-paste
   registry). Raw-Ark wrappers MUST still: set `data-slot`, read tokens
   via Tailwind aliases (no hardcoded hex), forward `className` last via
   `cn()`, and match the shadcn/Radix-shaped API the rest of `components/ui`
   exposes. Do NOT reimplement a Chakra v3-wrapped primitive in raw Ark
   just because Tark UI ships one — Chakra wrappers (Dialog, Menu, Select,
   Combobox, Tooltip, Tabs, Accordion, Popover, Switch, Checkbox, Radio
   Group, Slider, Toast, Avatar) stay canon.

## Anti-patterns and fixes

```tsx
// BAD — Chakra style props inside our wrapper
<ChakraSelect.Root colorPalette="blue" bg="bg.subtle">

// GOOD — Tailwind on the wrapped element
<ChakraSelect.Root>
  <ChakraSelect.Content className="bg-popover text-popover-foreground border border-border">
```

```tsx
// BAD — hardcoded color
<div className="bg-[#5865f2] text-white">

// GOOD — token via Tailwind alias
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
```

```tsx
// BAD — consumer reinvents controlled close
const [internalOpen, setInternalOpen] = useState(open)
useEffect(() => setInternalOpen(open), [open])
return <Dialog open={internalOpen} onOpenChange={setInternalOpen}>

// GOOD — trust the wrapper
return <Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={onOpenChange}>
```

```tsx
// BAD — render JSX inside Select.ValueText without itemToString
<Select.ValueText>{value}</Select.ValueText>

// GOOD — collection knows how to stringify, useSelectContext renders the label
const collection = createListCollection({
  items,
  itemToValue: (i) => i.id,
  itemToString: (i) => i.label,
})
```

```tsx
// BAD — reimplement an already-wrapped Chakra primitive in raw Ark
// just to ape Tark UI. Two layers, two bug surfaces, zero benefit.
import { Dialog as ArkDialog } from "@ark-ui/react/dialog"
export function Dialog(props) { return <ArkDialog.Root {...props} /> }

// GOOD — paste raw Ark + Tailwind only for primitives Chakra v3
// doesn't ship (Tour, Tags Input, Steps, Editable, Number Input, ...)
import { Steps } from "@ark-ui/react/steps"
export function Steps({ className, ...props }: StepsProps) {
  return (
    <Steps.Root data-slot="steps" className={cn("...", className)} {...props} />
  )
}
```

## When in doubt

If a Chakra component is fighting Tailwind, the wrapper is the place to fix it
once — not the consumer. Push the conflict down into `components/ui/*`, write
the workaround there (a recipe override, an Ark-direct drop-down, a token
mapping), and keep product code reading the same shadcn-shaped API.
